#. <section class="sutta" id="mn120"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn120:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 120"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 120"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn120:0.2"
msgid "Saṅkhārupapattisutta"
msgstr "Rebirth by Choice"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn120:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn120:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn120:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn120:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn120:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn120:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn120:2.1"
msgid "“saṅkhārupapattiṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, "
msgstr "“I shall teach you rebirth by choice. "

msgctxt "mn120:2.2"
msgid "taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn120:2.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn120:2.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.100"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn120:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena samannāgato "
"hoti, sutena samannāgato hoti, cāgena samannāgato hoti, paññāya samannāgato "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Take a mendicant who has faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom."

msgctxt "mn120:3.2"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "mn120:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ "
"upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of well-to-do aristocrats!’"

msgctxt "mn120:3.4"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr "They settle on that thought, stabilize it and develop it."

#. VAR: tatrupapattiyā → tatrūpapattiyā (bj, s1-3, km) | tatruppattiyā (pts1)
msgctxt "mn120:3.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa te saṅkhārā ca vihārā ca evaṃ bhāvitā evaṃ bahulīkatā tatrupapattiyā "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"Those choices and meditations of theirs, developed and cultivated like this, "
"lead to rebirth there."

msgctxt "mn120:3.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā tatrupapattiyā saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the path and the practice that leads to rebirth there."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4-5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn120:4-5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena "
"samannāgato hoti, sutena samannāgato hoti, cāgena samannāgato hoti, paññāya "
"samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who has faith, ethics, learning, generosity, "
"and wisdom."

msgctxt "mn120:4-5.2"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "mn120:4-5.3"
msgid "‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of well-to-do brahmins …"

msgctxt "mn120:4-5.4"
msgid "gahapatimahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr "well-to-do householders.’"

msgctxt "mn120:4-5.5"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr "They settle on that thought, stabilize it and develop it."

msgctxt "mn120:4-5.6"
msgid ""
"Tassa te saṅkhārā ca vihārā ca evaṃ bhāvitā evaṃ bahulīkatā tatrupapattiyā "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"Those choices and meditations of theirs, developed and cultivated like this, "
"lead to rebirth there."

msgctxt "mn120:4-5.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā tatrupapattiyā saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the path and the practice that leads to rebirth there."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena samannāgato hoti, sutena samannāgato hoti, cāgena samannāgato hoti, paññāya samannāgato hoti. → etthantare pāṭho syā1, syā2 potthakesu
msgctxt "mn120:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena "
"samannāgato hoti, sutena samannāgato hoti, cāgena samannāgato hoti, paññāya "
"samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who has faith, ethics, learning, generosity, "
"and wisdom."

msgctxt "mn120:6.2"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "And they’ve heard:"

#. VAR: cātumahārājikā → cātum­mahārā­jikā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn120:6.3"
msgid "‘cātumahārājikā devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Gods of the Four Great Kings are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’"

msgctxt "mn120:6.4"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "mn120:6.5"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ "
"upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of the Gods of the Four Great Kings!’"

msgctxt "mn120:6.6"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr "They settle on that thought, stabilize it and develop it."

msgctxt "mn120:6.7"
msgid ""
"Tassa te saṅkhārā ca vihārā ca evaṃ bhāvitā evaṃ bahulīkatā tatrupapattiyā "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"Those choices and meditations of theirs, developed and cultivated like this, "
"lead to rebirth there."

msgctxt "mn120:6.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā tatrupapattiyā saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the path and the practice that leads to rebirth there."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7-11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn120:7-11.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena "
"samannāgato hoti, sutena samannāgato hoti, cāgena samannāgato hoti, paññāya "
"samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who has faith, ethics, learning, generosity, "
"and wisdom."

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.2"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "And they’ve heard:"

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.3"
msgid "tāvatiṃsā devā … pe …"
msgstr "‘The Gods of the Thirty-Three …"

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.4"
msgid "yāmā devā …"
msgstr "the Gods of Yama …"

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.5"
msgid "tusitā devā …"
msgstr "the Joyful Gods …"

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.6"
msgid "nimmānaratī devā …"
msgstr "the Gods Who Love to Create …"

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.7"
msgid "paranimmitavasavattī devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulāti."
msgstr ""
"the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others are long-lived, beautiful, and "
"very happy.’"

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.8"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.9"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā paranimmitavasavattīnaṃ devānaṃ "
"sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others!’"

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.10"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr "They settle on that thought, stabilize it and develop it."

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.11"
msgid ""
"Tassa te saṅkhārā ca vihārā ca evaṃ bhāvitā evaṃ bahulīkatā tatrupapattiyā "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"Those choices and meditations of theirs, developed and cultivated like this, "
"lead to rebirth there."

msgctxt "mn120:7-11.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā tatrupapattiyā saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the path and the practice that leads to rebirth there."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.101"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn120:12.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena "
"samannāgato hoti, sutena samannāgato hoti, cāgena samannāgato hoti, paññāya "
"samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who has faith, ethics, learning, generosity, "
"and wisdom."

msgctxt "mn120:12.2"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "And they’ve heard:"

msgctxt "mn120:12.3"
msgid "‘sahasso brahmā dīghāyuko vaṇṇavā sukhabahulo’ti."
msgstr "‘The Brahmā of a thousand is long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’"

#. VAR: adhimuccitvā → adhimuñcitvā (mr)
msgctxt "mn120:12.4"
msgid ""
"Sahasso, bhikkhave, brahmā sahassilokadhātuṃ pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"Now the Brahmā of a thousand meditates resolved on pervading a galaxy of a "
"thousand solar systems,"

msgctxt "mn120:12.5"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr "as well as the sentient beings reborn there."

msgctxt "mn120:12.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, cakkhumā puriso ekaṃ āmaṇḍaṃ hatthe karitvā "
"paccavekkheyya;"
msgstr "As a person might pick up a gallnut in their hand and examine it,"

msgctxt "mn120:12.7"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, sahasso brahmā sahassilokadhātuṃ pharitvā "
"adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"so too the Brahmā of a thousand meditates resolved on pervading a galaxy of "
"a thousand solar systems,"

msgctxt "mn120:12.8"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr "as well as the sentient beings reborn there."

msgctxt "mn120:12.9"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "mn120:12.10"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sahassassa brahmuno sahabyataṃ "
"upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of the Brahmā of a thousand!’"

msgctxt "mn120:12.11"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr "They settle on that thought, stabilize it and develop it."

msgctxt "mn120:12.12"
msgid ""
"Tassa te saṅkhārā ca vihārā ca evaṃ bhāvitā evaṃ bahulīkatā tatrupapattiyā "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"Those choices and meditations of theirs, developed and cultivated like this, "
"lead to rebirth there."

msgctxt "mn120:12.13"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā tatrupapattiyā saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the path and the practice that leads to rebirth there."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13-16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn120:13-16.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena "
"samannāgato hoti, sutena …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who has faith, ethics, learning, generosity, "
"and wisdom."

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.2"
msgid "cāgena …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.3"
msgid "paññāya samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.4"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "And they’ve heard:"

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.5"
msgid "dvisahasso brahmā … pe …"
msgstr "‘The Brahmā of two thousand …"

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.6"
msgid "tisahasso brahmā …"
msgstr "the Brahmā of three thousand …"

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.7"
msgid "catusahasso brahmā …"
msgstr "the Brahmā of four thousand …"

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.8"
msgid "pañcasahasso brahmā dīghāyuko vaṇṇavā sukhabahuloti."
msgstr "the Brahmā of five thousand is long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’"

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.9"
msgid ""
"Pañcasahasso, bhikkhave, brahmā pañcasahassilokadhātuṃ pharitvā adhimuccitvā "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Now the Brahmā of five thousand meditates resolved on pervading a galaxy of "
"five thousand solar systems,"

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.10"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr "as well as the sentient beings reborn there."

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.11"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, cakkhumā puriso pañca āmaṇḍāni hatthe karitvā "
"paccavekkheyya;"
msgstr "As a person might pick up five gallnuts in their hand and examine them,"

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.12"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, pañcasahasso brahmā pañcasahassilokadhātuṃ pharitvā "
"adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"so too the Brahmā of five thousand meditates resolved on pervading a galaxy "
"of five thousand solar systems,"

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.13"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr "as well as the sentient beings reborn there."

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.14"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.15"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pañcasahassassa brahmuno sahabyataṃ "
"upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of the Brahmā of five thousand!’"

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.16"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr "They settle on that thought, stabilize it and develop it."

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.17"
msgid ""
"Tassa te saṅkhārā ca vihārā ca evaṃ bhāvitā evaṃ bahulīkatā tatrupapattiyā "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"Those choices and meditations of theirs, developed and cultivated like this, "
"lead to rebirth there."

msgctxt "mn120:13-16.18"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā tatrupapattiyā saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the path and the practice that leads to rebirth there."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.102"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn120:17.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena "
"samannāgato hoti, sutena …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who has faith, ethics, learning, generosity, "
"and wisdom."

msgctxt "mn120:17.2"
msgid "cāgena …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn120:17.3"
msgid "paññāya samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn120:17.4"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "And they’ve heard:"

msgctxt "mn120:17.5"
msgid "‘dasasahasso brahmā dīghāyuko vaṇṇavā sukhabahulo’ti."
msgstr "‘The Brahmā of ten thousand is long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’"

msgctxt "mn120:17.6"
msgid ""
"Dasasahasso, bhikkhave, brahmā dasasahassilokadhātuṃ pharitvā adhimuccitvā "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Now the Brahmā of ten thousand meditates resolved on pervading a galaxy of "
"ten thousand solar systems,"

msgctxt "mn120:17.7"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr "as well as the sentient beings reborn there."

#. VAR: bhāsate ca tapate ca → bhāsati ca tapati ca (s1-3, km) | bhāsati ca (pts1)
msgctxt "mn120:17.8"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato "
"paṇḍukambale nikkhitto bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a beryl gem that was naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, "
"with expert workmanship. When placed on a cream rug it would shine and glow "
"and radiate."

msgctxt "mn120:17.9"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, dasasahasso brahmā dasasahassilokadhātuṃ pharitvā "
"adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way the Brahmā of ten thousand meditates resolved on pervading a "
"galaxy of ten thousand solar systems,"

msgctxt "mn120:17.10"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr "as well as the sentient beings reborn there."

msgctxt "mn120:17.11"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "mn120:17.12"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā dasasahassassa brahmuno sahabyataṃ "
"upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of the Brahmā of ten thousand!’"

msgctxt "mn120:17.13"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr "They settle on that thought, stabilize it and develop it."

msgctxt "mn120:17.14"
msgid ""
"Tassa te saṅkhārā ca vihārā ca evaṃ bhāvitā evaṃ bahulīkatā tatrupapattiyā "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"Those choices and meditations of theirs, developed and cultivated like this, "
"lead to rebirth there."

msgctxt "mn120:17.15"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā tatrupapattiyā saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the path and the practice that leads to rebirth there."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn120:18.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who has faith, ethics, learning, generosity, "
"and wisdom."

msgctxt "mn120:18.2"
msgid "sutena …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn120:18.3"
msgid "cāgena …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn120:18.4"
msgid "paññāya samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn120:18.5"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "And they’ve heard:"

msgctxt "mn120:18.6"
msgid "‘satasahasso brahmā dīghāyuko vaṇṇavā sukhabahulo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Brahmā of a hundred thousand is long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’"

msgctxt "mn120:18.7"
msgid ""
"Satasahasso, bhikkhave, brahmā satasahassilokadhātuṃ pharitvā adhimuccitvā "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Now the Brahmā of a hundred thousand meditates resolved on pervading a "
"galaxy of a hundred thousand solar systems,"

msgctxt "mn120:18.8"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr "as well as the sentient beings reborn there."

#. VAR: nikkhaṃ → nekkhaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn120:18.9"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, nikkhaṃ jambonadaṃ "
"dakkhakammāraputtaukkāmukhasukusalasampahaṭṭhaṃ paṇḍukambale nikkhittaṃ "
"bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was an ornament of rare gold, fashioned by an expert smith, "
"expertly wrought in the forge. When placed on a cream rug it would shine and "
"glow and radiate."

msgctxt "mn120:18.10"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, satasahasso brahmā satasahassilokadhātuṃ pharitvā "
"adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way the Brahmā of a hundred thousand meditates resolved on "
"pervading a galaxy of a hundred thousand solar systems,"

msgctxt "mn120:18.11"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā tepi pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati."
msgstr "as well as the sentient beings reborn there."

msgctxt "mn120:18.12"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "mn120:18.13"
msgid ""
